ail":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Remediated blocker f631a32f98b89c858 and advisory f0110cea0acb56fee by replacing the ambiguous dry-run/healthy language with four real no-bypass fixture cases, exact exit/status/reason oracles, and a required structured JSON evidence object whose pass rule is deterministic. Applied f122e6d6015ac4594 and f61f04782931b67c6 by adding explicit negative-scope and depends_on/blocks-normalization ACs. Resolved f5b5c5d2b56577f0c by making sibling stories the sole config-schema/golden owners; this dogfood story verifies their combined result and does not redundantly edit the golden. Applied ff6e83eed6abfc202 by adding docs/release-notes.md to file impact.","timestamp":1784576417658350001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"PASS advisory dispositions: f341454a7ea5c3ef7 is accepted as an execution precondition. Do not claim or implement this dogfood story until 75de-02b0-d454-410b and 2bbd-87f6-8765-4b00 are closed and merged; before editing rebar.toml, require both keys to exist in VerifyConfig, _SECTIONS[\"verify\"], and tests/golden/config_surface.json, and require the stale-pin and close-plan enforcement paths to exist. Absence blocks execution as upstream contract drift. f2da24066da3ece5a and f5cc2e2b954a8f381 are accepted for execution: build the isolated tracker using the existing rebar_repo lifecycle fixture/temp-repo pattern, run `.venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/interfaces/lifecycle/`, and use the real CLI subprocess only for the four final public-surface cases because that specifically proves exit codes and user-visible remediation text. f2959f10b9af64816 is accepted: both release files are required deliverables.","timestamp":1784577036447280001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"{\"config\":{\"enforce_plan_material_pins\":true,\"require_plan_review_for_close\":true},\"cases\":[{\"name\":\"legacy_unpinned_claim_succeeds\",\"command\":\"python -m rebar.cli claim <legacy_ticket_id> --assignee=fixture\",\"expected_exit\":0,\"observed_exit\":0,\"before_status\":\"open\",\"expected_after_status\":\"in_progress\",\"observed_after_status\":\"in_progress\",\"expected_reason_tokens\":[],\"observed_reason\":\"\",\"passed\":true},{\"name\":\"current_pins_execution_review_close_succeeds\",\"command\":\"python -m rebar.cli transition <current_pinned_ticket_id> in_progress closed\",\"expected_exit\":0,\"observed_exit\":0,\"before_status\":\"in_progress\",\"expected_after_status\":\"closed\",\"observed_after_status\":\"closed\",\"expected_reason_tokens\":[],\"observed_reason\":\"\",\"passed\":true},{\"name\":\"stale_material_pin_drift_rejects_claim\",\"command\":\"python -m rebar.cli claim <stale_pinned_ticket_id> --assignee=fixture\",\"expected_exit\":1,\"observed_exit\":1,\"before_status\":\"open\",\"expected_after_status\":\"open\",\"observed_after_status\":\"open\",\"expected_reason_tokens\":[\"stale-pin-drift\",\"<canonical_prerequisite_id>\"],\"observed_reason\":\"reviewed related-ticket material is stale (stale-pin-drift; targets: <canonical_prerequisite_id>)\",\"passed\":true},{\"name\":\"planning_phase_close_review_rejects_close\",\"command\":\"python -m rebar.cli transition <planning_review_ticket_id> in_progress closed\",\"expected_exit\":1,\"observed_exit\":1,\"before_status\":\"in_progress\",\"expected_after_status\":\"in_progress\",\"observed_after_status\":\"in_progress\",\"expected_reason_tokens\":[\"incompatible-phase\",\"review-plan\"],\"observed_reason\":\"plan-review close gate rejected incompatible-phase review and instructed: Run rebar review-plan <planning_review_ticket_id> separately, then retry close.\",\"passed\":true}]}","timestamp":1784785277317723001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Completion verification against landed commit 7650f579b returned FAIL. Genuine repository-evidence gaps remain for public lifecycle coverage: natural A-to-B-to-C transitive invalidation; depends_on plus inbound blocks canonical de-duplication; plan-review return-to-open reset; code-only close freshness; enable/disable/re-enable; and deleted/archived pinned targets. Existing public coverage already proves concurrency recheck and audited force-close, but the remaining cases require committed lifecycle tests. Story stays in_progress; no force-close. Follow-up implementation and Gerrit review are underway.","timestamp":1784789135397482001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Fresh execution-phase plan review against merged 365345897 returned BLOCK with four overlapping findings covering two real missing public lifecycle proofs: unchanged successful re-review must not propagate invalidation downstream, and an in-progress self-edit must invalidate close until a fresh execution review. Gerrit 923 remains valid and merged; story stays in_progress. Adding those two focused tests in a follow-up change, then rerunning full gates, Gerrit review, plan review, and completion verification. The overlap-judge Anthropic 520 was retryable and treated as abstain; it did not determine the BLOCK.","timestamp":1784796218686047001}],"created_at":1784517384153584001,"creation_channel":"python","deps":[{"link_uuid":"7a4aa8f3-3828-443e-8f38-4d927a1aa1ed","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"2bbd-87f6-8765-4b00"},{"link_uuid":"ae834582-f946-4516-a724-9219882224a1","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"7c27-10fc-4fe6-4b56"},{"link_uuid":"2ea88628-da50-4377-9ecf-6cd368868b35","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"cb6b-24b4-1056-4ee6"}],"description":"# Dogfood the completed lifecycle in rebar\n\n## Goal\nProve the integrated behavior through public surfaces and enable both optional policies for this project without requiring migration or backfill.\n\n## Implementation\n- Enable verify.enforce_plan_material_pins and verify.require_plan_review_for_close in rebar.toml; retain false defaults in the reusable configuration schema.\n- Add public-surface lifecycle scenarios for: legacy unpinned attestations; emission while enforcement is off; enable/disable/re-enable; direct child drift; depends_on and blocks normalization; natural A-to-B-to-C transitivity; successful unchanged re-review stopping propagation; execution-time self-edit; in_progress-to-open reset; code-only drift at close; deleted and archived pinned targets; concurrent review/close changes; and audited force-close.\n- Verify no eager backfill, graph-wide invalidation event, new pin command, list-output change, or stored relation migration occurs.\n- Treat the sibling stories as the sole owners of adding each configuration key to the reusable schema and `tests/golden/config_surface.json`. This story verifies both keys are already present together, enables them only in `rebar.toml`, and updates `CHANGELOG.md` plus `docs/release-notes.md` for the rebar-project policy cutover; it does not re-register either golden key.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Rebar enables both policies while library defaults remain off, and a pre-feature unpinned attestation continues to pass both gates.\n- [ ] End-to-end tests prove direct and natural-transitive invalidation only after actual narrow material changes.\n- [ ] An unchanged successful re-review produces no further propagation.\n- [ ] Outgoing `depends_on` and inbound `blocks` references to one canonical prerequisite normalize to one prerequisite pin/evaluation.\n- [ ] Execution adaptation, return-to-open reset, and code-only close freshness are proven through public lifecycle surfaces.\n- [ ] Enable, disable, and re-enable behavior is proven through public lifecycle surfaces.\n- [ ] Deleted and archived target handling, concurrency rechecks, and audited force-close are proven through public lifecycle surfaces.\n- [ ] No eager backfill, graph-wide invalidation event, new pin command, ordinary-list output change, or stored relation migration is introduced.\n\n## Verification\n- Run the complete lifecycle interface suite with both rebar policies enabled.\n- Run make check and the full non-integration test suite.\n- In an isolated fixture tracker, invoke the real checkout CLI with no `--dry-run` bypass and both policies loaded as `true`. Exercise four cases: (1) a legacy unpinned attestation claims successfully with exit 0 and `open -> in_progress`; (2) current pins plus compatible execution-phase plan and completion attestations close successfully with exit 0 and `in_progress -> closed`; (3) stale material-pin drift rejects claim or close with exit 1, leaves status unchanged, and names the canonical stale target plus `stale-pin-drift`; (4) missing or phase-incompatible close-plan review rejects close with exit 1, leaves `in_progress` unchanged, and instructs the operator to run `review-plan`. Do not use force-close in these four gate-health cases.\n- Record one JSON object in a ticket comment with `config.enforce_plan_material_pins`, `config.require_plan_review_for_close`, and a `cases` array. Each case contains `name`, `command`, `expected_exit`, `observed_exit`, `before_status`, `expected_after_status`, `observed_after_status`, `expected_reason_tokens`, `observed_reason`, and `passed`. Gate health passes only when both config fields are `true`, every observed exit/status exactly equals its expected value, every required reason token is present, and all four `passed` values are true. Any mismatch fails verification and blocks closing this story.\n","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"rebar.toml","reason":"Enable both optional policies for the rebar project."},{"path":"tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_plan_review_gate.py","reason":"Prove the integrated claim and close lifecycle."},{"path":"tests/unit/test_config_typed.py","reason":"Protect false defaults and enabled project configuration."},{"path":"CHANGELOG.md","reason":"Record the new opt-in behavior and rebar dogfood posture."},{"path":"docs/release-notes.md","reason":"Record the agent-visible activation of both rebar project policy gates."}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","2bbd-87f6-8765-4b00"],["depends_on","7c27-10fc-4fe6-4b56"],["depends_on","cb6b-24b4-1056-4ee6"],["parent","jira-reb-1160"]],"parent_id":"jira-reb-1160","parent_status_uuid":"231bcdf6-10cd-44a4-839e-d23ae8fb0979","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["plan-review","jira-reb-1160"],"ticket_id":"145e-52a9-26e3-4209","ticket_type":"story","title":"Enable material-pin and close-review enforcement for rebar with lifecycle acceptance coverage","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["37084eb5-65af-485e-a328-7b36d76b06b1","db301446-71e6-4924-9a77-337f70008481","7a4aa8f3-3828-443e-8f38-4d927a1aa1ed","ae834582-f946-4516-a724-9219882224a1","2ea88628-da50-4377-9ecf-6cd368868b35","0eddc3a5-7a5f-4f7b-bc1a-82d40d8449f6","688709c9-2829-4781-9740-6b6d4159d689","3f537ecb-576b-4451-8eea-599ba4fe6a38","6e83a001-32eb-4a10-af16-2ef933c58ecc","62b01510-00da-4251-bd97-98a0ebcfbe30","231bcdf6-10cd-44a4-839e-d23ae8fb0979","0f04f226-1993-4d68-9e14-13989db7e45b","5d7d1875-27c3-4b3d-aebb-b55a382567eb","a590fda5-5bec-45b9-8642-6ce5c9f1b169","958ccd7a-0723-48fa-8651-389b8c22f35b","85f4222b-f5e2-4ee5-bdb0-a2b33ddb9fad","ea08a43c-51be-4c2a-8883-0cb98e40ec11"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784796218686047002,"uuid":"3d8d3f8a-3f57-4429-8601-224b671dd8e2"}